{"key":"processedPost-12772431","value":{"id":12772431,"first":12761187,"last":12773054,"when":1277039793,"utime":"06/20/10 04:16 PM","content":"After full colonization, I'd wait a week and then cut the top off the bag for fruiting.&nbsp; Some strains are more CO2 tolerant than others, but many won't fruit with the only air being what exchanges through the tyvek patch on the bags.&nbsp; Open the top of the bag and lay a sheet of wax paper loosely over the top to help hold in humidity.&nbsp; Lift it up&nbsp; to fan and mist the contents daily and then replace.&nbsp; As the mushrooms grow, they'll push the wax paper up and out of the way.<br />RR","title":"Re: I think I got this grow bag thing right...... ??","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}